Metric: Net Revenue Retention
Description: Measures the percentage of recurring revenue retained from existing customers over a period, including expansion (upgrades, cross-sells) and contraction (downgrades, churn). A value above 100% indicates net expansion.
Owner: revenue-ops
Tags: nrr, retention, expansion, saas, board-metric

Source: subscriptions, subscription_events

Given we are looking at customers who had active subscriptions at the start of the period
  And we include only paid plans (excluding trials)
  And we track the same cohort of customers across the full period

When we calculate
  Then take the starting MRR for the cohort at period begin
  And add expansion MRR from upgrades and cross-sells during the period
  And subtract contraction MRR from downgrades during the period
  And subtract churned MRR from cancellations and expirations
  And divide the ending cohort MRR by the starting cohort MRR
  And multiply by 100

The result is "Net Revenue Retention"

Trust:
  Freshness must be less than 12 hours
  Null rate on plan_amount must be less than 0%
  Null rate on event_type must be less than 0%
  Row count of subscription_events must not drop more than 20% day over day
  Value must be between 50 and 200
  Value must not change more than 25% month over month
